 competing north and south korean states and the destructive war that followed constitute one of the great and still unresolved tragedies of the 20th century peacemaker is the memoir of lim dong won former south korean unification minister and architect of nobel peace prize winner kim dae jung's sunshine policy toward north korea as both witness and participant lim traces the process of twenty years of diplomatic negotiations with north korea from the earliest rounds of inter korean talks through the historic inter korean summit of june 2000 and beyond peacemaker offers a fascinating inside look into the recent history of north south korea relations and provides important lessons for policymakers and citizens who seek to understand and resolve the tragic and increasingly dangerous situation on the korean peninsula topics history north korea south korea search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages publications of interest politics of nationalism in us korean relations the gi wook shin paul yunsik chang asian perspective vol 28 2004 cover north korea and contending south korean identities analysis of the south korean media policy implications for the united states gi wook shin kristin c burke korea economic institute of america academic paper series on korea vol 1 2009 pdf+ cover to the brink of peace new challenges in inter korean economic cooperation and integration henry s rowen william j perry bradley babson nicholas eberstadt peter hayes jeong woo kil won bae kim lawrence j lau kiseok lee shorenstein aparc 2001 cover korean food korean identity the impact of globalization on korean agriculture john feffer shorenstein aparc 2005 pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
